  "text": "For the reverse inclusion, we first note additional results proved in [CITATION_1] and continue the notation of §2. Consider the 4-dimensional space V l R% equipped with the inner product of signature (3, 1) as before, so that we have an embedding µ of Γ(P) into O(V ). As this leaves the K(P)-lattice M(P) invariant, then µ(Γ(P)) is definable over K(P). Now let us consider again Γ + (P) 9 PSL(2, C). Let σ be a reflection in one of the faces of P so that the centraliser C(σ) of σ in Γ + (P) will stabilise the hyperbolic plane H which is spanned by the face of P. C(σ) has finite covolume acting on H but may contain reflections. However, it contains a non-elementary Fuchsian subgroup F of index 2 and choosing a pair of non-commuting elements in F (#) as generators for the quaternion algebra AP over kP (see [CITATION_2] ), we have that",
